   The dispute between Iraq and Kuwait began
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   when Iraq accused Kuwait of flooding the oil market and stealing $2.4 billion worth of oil.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   On July 20, Kuwaiti officials responded that Iraq wanted them to forgive war debts.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   On July 24, the United States announced a "short- notice exercise" in the Persian Gulf and Kuwait went on alert.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Saddam Hussein then summoned the U.S. ambassador for talks.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   OPEC ministers then agreed to halt overproduction and the two nations met to negotiate,
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   although 100,000 Iraqi troops were on the border.
  </a>
